jnxDfc.name: jnxDfc
jnxDfc.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
jnxDfc.description: This is Juniper Networks' implementation of enterprise specific MIB for Dynamic Flow Capture (DFC)

jnxDfcCSEntry.name: jnxDfcCSEntry
jnxDfcCSEntry.description: An entry of DFC Control Source table.

jnxDfcGrpName.name: jnxDfcGrpName
jnxDfcGrpName.description: The name assigned to a DFC group. A DFC group defines a set of DFC PICs that share same static/dynamic configuration.

jnxDfcCSId.name: jnxDfcCSId
jnxDfcCSId.description: Control Source identifier. Control Source identifies Juniper router with one unique Control IP address. There can be multiple IP addresses from which a Control Source can send Control protocol request to Juniper router.

jnxDfcCSControlProtocolAddRequests.name: jnxDfcCSControlProtocolAddRequests
jnxDfcCSControlProtocolAddRequests.description: Total number of Control protocol Add requests received. The add request specifies a new filter criteria to be merged with the existing tasking list for a given Control Source and Content Destination.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaAdded.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaAdded
jnxDfcCSCriteriaAdded.description: Total number of filter criteria added successfully by the Control Source.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaAdditionFailed.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaAdditionFailed
jnxDfcCSCriteriaAdditionFailed.description: Total number of filter criteria addition failed.

jnxDfcCSControlProtocolDeleteRequests.name: jnxDfcCSControlProtocolDeleteRequests
jnxDfcCSControlProtocolDeleteRequests.description: Total number of Control protocol delete requests received. The delete request removes a particular filter criterion.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeleted.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeleted
jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeleted.description: Total number of filter criteria deleted successfully as requested by Control Source.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletionFailed.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletionFailed
jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletionFailed.description: Total number of filter criteria deletion failed.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedTimeoutIdle.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedTimeoutIdle
jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedTimeoutIdle.description: Total number of criteria deleted by timeout idle.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedTimeoutTotal.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedTimeoutTotal
jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedTimeoutTotal.description: Total number of criteria deleted by timeout total.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedPackets.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedPackets
jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedPackets.description: Total number of criteria deleted by packets.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedBytes.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedBytes
jnxDfcCSCriteriaDeletedBytes.description: Total number of criteria deleted by bytes.

jnxDfcCSControlProtocolRefreshRequests.name: jnxDfcCSControlProtocolRefreshRequests
jnxDfcCSControlProtocolRefreshRequests.description: Total number of Control protocol Refresh requests received. The refresh request updates the timeout for a particular filter criterion or set of filter criteria for the particular Control Source to a particular Content Destination.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaRefreshed.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaRefreshed
jnxDfcCSCriteriaRefreshed.description: Total number of filter criteria refreshed successfully as requested by Control Source.

jnxDfcCSCriteriaRefreshFailed.name: jnxDfcCSCriteriaRefreshFailed
jnxDfcCSCriteriaRefreshFailed.description: Total number of filter criteria refresh request failed.

jnxDfcCSControlProtocolListRequests.name: jnxDfcCSControlProtocolListRequests
jnxDfcCSControlProtocolListRequests.description: Total number of Control protocol List requests received. The List request returns a list of all criteria that a particular Control Source has added and are currently active.

jnxDfcCSListSuccess.name: jnxDfcCSListSuccess
jnxDfcCSListSuccess.description: Total number of list commands processed successfully as requested by Control Source.

jnxDfcCSListFailed.name: jnxDfcCSListFailed
jnxDfcCSListFailed.description: Total number of list commands that could not be processed successfully.

jnxDfcCSControlProtocolNoopRequests.name: jnxDfcCSControlProtocolNoopRequests
jnxDfcCSControlProtocolNoopRequests.description: Total number of Control protocol Noop requests received. The purpose of this request is to verify the end-to-end connectivity between Control Source and DFC PIC.

jnxDfcCSNoopSuccess.name: jnxDfcCSNoopSuccess
jnxDfcCSNoopSuccess.description: Total number of Noop requests processed successfully as requested by Control Source.

jnxDfcCSNoopFailed.name: jnxDfcCSNoopFailed
jnxDfcCSNoopFailed.description: Total number of Noop requests that could not be processed successfully.

jnxDfcCSDynamicCriteriaActive.name: jnxDfcCSDynamicCriteriaActive
jnxDfcCSDynamicCriteriaActive.description: Total number of active dynamic filter criteria.

jnxDfcCSStaticCriteriaActive.name: jnxDfcCSStaticCriteriaActive
jnxDfcCSStaticCriteriaActive.description: Total number of active static filter criteria.

jnxDfcCSBadRequest.name: jnxDfcCSBadRequest
jnxDfcCSBadRequest.description: Total number of Bad requests received.

jnxDfcCSResponseSuccessful.name: jnxDfcCSResponseSuccessful
jnxDfcCSResponseSuccessful.description: Total number of successful response(s) corresponding to the requests (add, delete, refresh, list and noop) sent out to the Control Source.

jnxDfcCSResponseImproperCriteria.name: jnxDfcCSResponseImproperCriteria
jnxDfcCSResponseImproperCriteria.description: Total number of response(s) generated because of improper filter criterion specification in the add request.

jnxDfcCSResponseUnknownContentDest.name: jnxDfcCSResponseUnknownContentDest
jnxDfcCSResponseUnknownContentDest.description: Total number of response(s) generated because of unknown Content Destination specified in the add, delete, refresh and list request.

jnxDfcCSResponseUnknownCriteriaId.name: jnxDfcCSResponseUnknownCriteriaId
jnxDfcCSResponseUnknownCriteriaId.description: Total number of response(s) generated because of unknown Criteria Identifier specified in the delete, refresh and list request.

jnxDfcCSResponseImproperTimeout.name: jnxDfcCSResponseImproperTimeout
jnxDfcCSResponseImproperTimeout.description: Total number of response(s) generated because of improper timeout specified in the add and refresh request.

jnxDfcCSResponseInvalidAuthentication.name: jnxDfcCSResponseInvalidAuthentication
jnxDfcCSResponseInvalidAuthentication.description: Total number of response(s) generated because of invalid authentication specified in the add, delete, refresh, list and noop request.

jnxDfcCSResponseInvalidSequenceNumber.name: jnxDfcCSResponseInvalidSequenceNumber
jnxDfcCSResponseInvalidSequenceNumber.description: Total number of response(s) generated because of invalid Sequence Number specified in the add, delete, refresh, list and noop request.

jnxDfcCSResponseInternalError.name: jnxDfcCSResponseInternalError
jnxDfcCSResponseInternalError.description: Total number of response(s) generated because of internal error at the DFC PIC in processing a request.

jnxDfcCSNotificationRestart.name: jnxDfcCSNotificationRestart
jnxDfcCSNotificationRestart.description: Total number of Restart notifications sent to configured notification-recipients. This notification will be generated when the system experiences a failure such that all the DFC filter criteria are lost.

jnxDfcCSNotificationRollover.name: jnxDfcCSNotificationRollover
jnxDfcCSNotificationRollover.description: Total number of Rollover notifications sent to configured notification-recipients. This notification will be generated when the DFC PIC experiences a sequence number rollover.

jnxDfcCSNotificationNoop.name: jnxDfcCSNotificationNoop
jnxDfcCSNotificationNoop.description: Total number of Noop notifications sent to configured notification-recipents. This notification will be generated when the DFC PIC receives a Noop message with the SendAsync parameter present.

jnxDfcCSNotificationTimeout.name: jnxDfcCSNotificationTimeout
jnxDfcCSNotificationTimeout.description: Total number of Timeout notifications sent to configured notification-recipents. This notification will be generated when the DFC PIC times out a filter criterion on any one of its configured timeout parameters and the criterion contains a SendTimeoutAsync parameter.

jnxDfcCSNotificationCongestion.name: jnxDfcCSNotificationCongestion
jnxDfcCSNotificationCongestion.description: Total number of Congestion notifications sent to configured notification-recipents. This notification will be generated when the 10-second average packet forwarding rate (in bits/second) summed over all active filter criteria to a configured Content Destination exceeds the configured soft limit for that destination.

jnxDfcCSNotificationCongestionDelete.name: jnxDfcCSNotificationCongestionDelete
jnxDfcCSNotificationCongestionDelete.description: Total number of Congestion Delete notifications sent to configured notification-recipents. This notification will be generated when the total 10-second average packet forwarding rate (in bits/second) summed over all active filter criteria to a configured Content Destination exceeds the configured hard limit for that destination.

jnxDfcCSNotificationDuplicatesDropped.name: jnxDfcCSNotificationDuplicatesDropped
jnxDfcCSNotificationDuplicatesDropped.description: Total number of Duplicates Dropped notifications sent to configured notification-recipents. This notification will be generated when the configurable Maximum Duplicates parameter has been exceeded in such a way as to cause packets matching criteria added by the corresponding Control Source to be dropped.

jnxDfcCSAddRequestPeakRate.name: jnxDfcCSAddRequestPeakRate
jnxDfcCSAddRequestPeakRate.description: The peak request processing rate (requests processed/second).

jnxDfcCDEntry.name: jnxDfcCDEntry
jnxDfcCDEntry.description: An entry of DFC Content-Destination table.

jnxDfcCDId.name: jnxDfcCDId
jnxDfcCDId.description: Content Destination identifier. A Content Destination is the recipient of the extracted data, once it is forwarded by the Server.

jnxDfcCDCriteria.name: jnxDfcCDCriteria
jnxDfcCDCriteria.description: Total number of filter criteria configured for the Content Destination.

jnxDfcCDByteRate.name: jnxDfcCDByteRate
jnxDfcCDByteRate.description: Average data rate (in bytes/second) summed over all active filter criteria to a configured Content Destination.

jnxDfcCDMatchedPackets.name: jnxDfcCDMatchedPackets
jnxDfcCDMatchedPackets.description: Total number of packets matching the filter criteria configured for the Content Destination.

jnxDfcCDMatchedBytes.name: jnxDfcCDMatchedBytes
jnxDfcCDMatchedBytes.description: Total number of bytes matching the filter criteria configured for the Content Destination.

jnxDfcCDCongestionNotification.name: jnxDfcCDCongestionNotification
jnxDfcCDCongestionNotification.description: Total number of Congestion Notifications sent to a configured notification-recipient.

jnxDfcInterfaceName.name: jnxDfcInterfaceName
jnxDfcInterfaceName.description: The textual name of the DFC interface.

jnxDfcInputPktRate.name: jnxDfcInputPktRate
jnxDfcInputPktRate.description: data packet rate (in packets per second).

jnxDfcPpsSoftOverloadLowWatermark.name: jnxDfcPpsSoftOverloadLowWatermark
jnxDfcPpsSoftOverloadLowWatermark.description: Configured lowest value for data packet rate (in packets per second).

jnxDfcPpsSoftOverloadHighWatermark.name: jnxDfcPpsSoftOverloadHighWatermark
jnxDfcPpsSoftOverloadHighWatermark.description: Configured highest value for data packet rate (in packets per second).

jnxDfcPpsHardOverloadLowWatermark.name: jnxDfcPpsHardOverloadLowWatermark
jnxDfcPpsHardOverloadLowWatermark.description: Recommended lowest value for data packet rate (in packets per second).

jnxDfcPpsHardOverloadHighWatermark.name: jnxDfcPpsHardOverloadHighWatermark
jnxDfcPpsHardOverloadHighWatermark.description: Recommended highest value for data packet rate (in packets per second).

jnxDfcFlowsUsage.name: jnxDfcFlowsUsage
jnxDfcFlowsUsage.description: % usage of total number of flows in system.

jnxDfcCriteriaUsage.name: jnxDfcCriteriaUsage
jnxDfcCriteriaUsage.description: % usage of matching criteria for all filters.

jnxDfcMemSoftOverloadLowWatermark.name: jnxDfcMemSoftOverloadLowWatermark
jnxDfcMemSoftOverloadLowWatermark.description: Configured lowest watermark percent for memory load.

jnxDfcMemSoftOverloadHighWatermark.name: jnxDfcMemSoftOverloadHighWatermark
jnxDfcMemSoftOverloadHighWatermark.description: Configured highest watermark percent for memory load.

jnxDfcFlowLowWatermark.name: jnxDfcFlowLowWatermark
jnxDfcFlowLowWatermark.description: Recommended lowest value for number of flows allowed in the system.

jnxDfcFlowHighWatermark.name: jnxDfcFlowHighWatermark
jnxDfcFlowHighWatermark.description: Recommended highest value for number of flows allowed in the system.

jnxDfcCriteriaLowWatermark.name: jnxDfcCriteriaLowWatermark
jnxDfcCriteriaLowWatermark.description: Recommended lowest value for number of criterias allowed in the system.

jnxDfcCriteriaHighWatermark.name: jnxDfcCriteriaHighWatermark
jnxDfcCriteriaHighWatermark.description: Recommended highest value for number of criterias allowed in the system.

jnxDfcNotificationPrefix.name: jnxDfcNotificationPrefix
jnxDfcNotificationPrefix.description: All DFC notifications are registered under this branch.

jnxDfcSoftPpsThresholdExceeded.name: jnxDfcSoftPpsThresholdExceeded
jnxDfcSoftPpsThresholdExceeded.description: Notification of input packet rate (in packet per second) going beyond the configured limit.

jnxDfcSoftPpsUnderThreshold.name: jnxDfcSoftPpsUnderThreshold
jnxDfcSoftPpsUnderThreshold.description: Notification of input packet rate (in packet per second) dropping back to below the configured limit.

jnxDfcHardPpsThresholdExceeded.name: jnxDfcHardPpsThresholdExceeded
jnxDfcHardPpsThresholdExceeded.description: Notification of input packet rate (in packet per second) going beyond the recommended limit.

jnxDfcHardPpsUnderThreshold.name: jnxDfcHardPpsUnderThreshold
jnxDfcHardPpsUnderThreshold.description: Notification of input packet rate (in packet per second) dropping back to below the recommended limit.

jnxDfcSoftMemThresholdExceeded.name: jnxDfcSoftMemThresholdExceeded
jnxDfcSoftMemThresholdExceeded.description: Notification of memory overload condition i.e memory usage is going beyond the configured limit.

jnxDfcSoftMemUnderThreshold.name: jnxDfcSoftMemUnderThreshold
jnxDfcSoftMemUnderThreshold.description: Notification of memory usage dropping back to below the configured limit.

jnxDfcHardMemThresholdExceeded.name: jnxDfcHardMemThresholdExceeded
jnxDfcHardMemThresholdExceeded.description: Notification of memory overload condition i.e memory usage is going beyond the recommended limit.

jnxDfcHardMemUnderThreshold.name: jnxDfcHardMemUnderThreshold
jnxDfcHardMemUnderThreshold.description: Notification of memory usage dropping back to below the recommended limit.
